# Cursor AI Rules - Universal AI Memory Integration

## AUTOMATIC CONTEXT LOADING
Before providing any assistance, automatically read these files if they exist:
- .ai-instructions (project-specific AI instructions)
- .ai/project-overview.md (project context)
- .ai/conversation-log.md (previous conversations and decisions)
- .ai/technical-decisions.md (why we chose X over Y)
- .ai/next-steps.md (current priorities)
- .aicf/README.md (AI-optimized memory format instructions)
- .aicf/*.aicf (AI-optimized memory files)

## SESSION START PROTOCOL
1. Check for .ai/ or .aicf/ directories
2. If found, read all context files before responding
3. Confirm understanding of project state
4. Continue work with full context

## SESSION END PROTOCOL
At session end:
1. Update .ai/conversation-log.md with key decisions from this session
2. Update .ai/technical-decisions.md with any architectural choices made
3. Update .ai/next-steps.md with current priorities
4. Or run `npx aic finish --aicf` for automated processing

This implements the Universal AI Memory System by Dennis van Leeuwen.